</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="33.[151,1437,1432,1745]" pageId="33" pageNumber="484">
Radula 
<quantity box="[287,375,1504,1529]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.6" pageId="33" pageNumber="484" unit="mm" value="1.6">1.6 mm</quantity>
long with 32 transverse rows of mature teeth in studied specimen (BL 
<quantity box="[1195,1267,1504,1529]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.0" pageId="33" pageNumber="484" unit="mm" value="5.0">5 mm</quantity>
). Central tooth elongate tulip-shaped with weakly bilobed blade, keeled at basal half. First lateral (centro-lateral) tooth with thickened antero-dorsal corner. Major lateral tooth with tricuspid head; cusps rather thin, sharply pointed. Major uncinus tooth with rather wide blade.
</paragraph>
