<subSubSection pageId="33" pageNumber="484" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="33.[151,1437,1432,1745]" pageId="33" pageNumber="484">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1684,1709]" pageId="33" pageNumber="484">Remarks.</emphasis>
The present species differs from all other Indo-West Pacific 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Gray" authorityYear="1821" box="[1022,1199,1684,1709]" class="Polyplacophora" family="Acanthochitonidae" genus="Acanthochitona" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chitonida" pageId="33" pageNumber="484" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1022,1199,1684,1709]" italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="484">Acanthochitona</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species by having a very narrow jugum and strongly curved spicules on the perinotum.
</paragraph>
